 &\leq - \frac{4\omega-\sup a^2}{4}<0.
\end{align*}
Therefore, $h$ is strictly decreasing and can achieve any negative number. In particular,  

for some $t_0\geq 0$, $h(t_0)<\min\{0,\inf a\}$. Consequently for $t>t_0$,
\begin{align*}
h' & < -h( h - \inf a).
\end{align*}
Since $h(t_0)<\min\{0,\inf a\}$, it admits a Riccati type blowup. Indeed on comparing above differential inequality with an equality, we obtain $\lim_{t\to t_c^-} h(t) = -\infty$ for some $t_c < t_0 - (h(t_0))^{-1}$.

