Let $t_*$ be the first negative time such that $\hat q'(t_*) = 0$. Then $\hat q(t_*)<1/\rho_{max}$ if and only if 
\begin{align}
\label{l1clocon2}
& (\beta_{max}-\beta_{min}) \left( 1 + e^{-\frac{\pi}{\tilde z}} \right) e^{- \frac{\tan^{-1}(\hat z)}{\hat z}} < \sqrt{kc}\left( 1-\frac{c}{\rho_{max}} \right)\left(1- e^{-\frac{\pi}{\hat z}-\frac{\pi}{\tilde z}}  \right) .
\end{align}

nodes.proof:
For $\rho_{max}+\rho_{min} = 2c$, we have $\gamma_1,\gamma_2$ in Lemma \ref{psistarnewboundslem} being equal to $\gamma$ and, therefore, $S = 2\rho_{max}(||\psi||_1 - 2\gamma)/\sqrt{kc}$. Moreover, noting the expressions from \eqref{hattildez}, we also have for $0<\rho_{min}<c<\rho_{max}<2c$ that,
\begin{subequations}
\label{betabounds}
\begin{align}
& ||\psi||_1 c > \beta_{min} = (||\psi||_1 - 2\gamma) \rho_{min} + 2c\gamma > 2\gamma c, \label{betabounds1} \\
& ||\psi||_1 c < \beta_{max} = (||\psi||_1 - 2\gamma) \rho_{max} + 2c\gamma < 2(||\psi||_1 - \gamma)c < 2 ||\psi||_1 c. \label{betabounds2}
\end{align}
\end{subequations}
Consequently, the expressions in \eqref{hattildez} have the following bounds,
\begin{align}
\label{zbounds}
& \sqrt{\frac{4k}{||\psi||_1^2 c} - 1}< \hat z < \tilde z < \sqrt{\frac{k}{\gamma^2 c} - 1}.
\end{align}

We first focus our attention on \eqref{condrewr1}. For right hand side of the inequality,
\begin{align*}
\frac{e^{\frac{\tan^{-1}\hat z}{\hat z}} \left( 1 - e^{-\frac{\pi}{\tilde z} - \frac{\pi}{\hat z}} \right)}{\left( 1 + e^{- \frac{\pi}{\tilde z}} \right)}& > \frac{e^{\frac{\tan^{-1}\tilde z}{\tilde z}} \left( 1 - e^{-\frac{2\pi}{\tilde z} } \right)}{\left( 1 + e^{- \frac{\pi}{\tilde z}} \right)} =: h(\tilde z) \label{hdef} \numberthis\\
& > h\left(\sqrt{\frac{k}{\gamma^2 c} - 1}\right) > 0.
\end{align*}
Here, we use the fact that $h$ is a decreasing function for nonnegative argument. 
Observing that $h\left(\sqrt{\frac{k}{\gamma^2 c} - 1}\right)$ increases as $\gamma$ increases, we then have,
$$
S < 4\sqrt{\frac{c}{k}}(||\psi||_1 - 2\gamma) < h\left(\sqrt{\frac{k}{\gamma^2 c} - 1}\right) < \frac{e^{\frac{\tan^{-1}\hat z}{\hat z}} \left( 1 - e^{-\frac{\pi}{\tilde z} - \frac{\pi}{\hat z}} \right)}{\left( 1 + e^{- \frac{\pi}{\tilde z}} \right)},
$$
for all $\rho_{max},\rho_{min}$. Also, with $\rho_{max}+\rho_{min}=2c$ \eqref{condrewr2} can be simplified to,
$$
S\geq e\left( e^{0.3(\tilde z - \hat z)} - e^{-\frac{\pi}{\tilde z}}\frac{\rho_{max}}{\rho_{min}} \right).
$$
Using \eqref{zbounds}, we note that if $\rho_{max}\nearrow 2c$, $\rho_{min}\searrow 0$, then the right hand side tends to negative infinity. Also, since $\rho_{max}>c$, we have $S> 2\sqrt{\frac{c}{k}}(||\psi||_1 - 2\gamma)$. Hence, we obtain that for some $\rho_{max},\rho_{min}$, the following holds,
$$
S  > e\left( e^{0.3(\tilde z - \hat z)} - e^{-\frac{\pi}{\tilde z}}\frac{\rho_{max}}{\rho_{min}} \right).
$$

This finishes the proof of the Lemma.
